+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]destinyland writes "YouTube just has signed [1]a deal to share ad
revenue with 20-year-old Brandon Fletcher. YouTube had already said
they'd implement revenue sharing this summer, but this indicates they're
willing to put their money where their mouth was. 10 Zen Monkeys has [2]a
funny chronicle of Brandon's enviable march to YouTube money. 9 weeks ago
he flew to California to demand YouTube feature his video on their front
page. A security guard refused to let him off the elevator — but he made
crucial contacts which helped seal the deal 9 weeks later. Taking this
business to the next level makes sense in the here and now, when some
[3]70 percent of internet users are streaming video."

