| Quantum Dots Might Be Key For Teleportation                        |
|   from the trek-is-now dept.                                       |
|   posted by Zonk on Sunday June 24, @03:34 (Science)               |
|   http://science.slashdot.org/article.pl?sid=07/06/24/068227       |
+--------------------------------------------------------------------+

[0]prostoalex writes "Researchers from Nanyang Technological University
in Singapore have created [1]a model teleportation system using quantum
dots. PhysOrg reports that 'tiny clusters of atoms known as quantum dots
may be excellent media for quantum teleportation, a physics phenomenon in
which information — in the form of a quantum state, a very specific
mathematical signature of an atom — can be transmitted almost
instantaneously to a distant location without having to physically travel
through space.'"

Discuss this story at:
    http://science.slashdot.org/comments.pl?sid=07/06/24/068227

